	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You shuffle a stone, twig, and bit of greenery around, and as you do so, the world around you seems to change.</em></p><p><strong>Illusory Image</strong></p><p>Roll an &amp;Reference[illusoryimages]{illusion check} for this spell.</p><ul><li><p>You create an illusion over terrain. Within the illusion, you can change the appearance of surfaces, as well as ambient sounds and smells.</p></li><li><p>You can alter the appearance of the shape of surfaces in minor ways, such as making illusory grass sway in the wind or making a door look like a wall, but you can't hide a hole larger than a 10 ft. in any dimension, nor can you make it appear as if there are holes where there weren't any.</p></li><li><p>You can make terrain appear like &amp;reference[difficult terrain], but you can't make a liquid look like a solid or vice versa.</p></li><li><p>The terrain's physical characteristics remain unchanged; if a creature touches any part of the illusion that would not make sense physically (such as touching a door handle you concealed), the creature automatically disbelieves the illusion.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
